Sharding of Database:

Database sharding is a key component for scaling both SQL and Non-SQL databases. According to the name, the database is sliced up into multiple pieces which are also called shards.

Each of the shards has a unique index that corresponds to the type of data that is to be stored. Check the example section to understand this concept.


